Road at the Forest's Edge~
A narrow road winds its way through the shadows of the hills, its aged
surface covered in scars and potholes.  Rising to the north, a viridian
pine woodland stretches a reasonable way to the west until it reaches the
valley's cliffside edge.  Beyond the forest, the snow covered flanks of a
massive mountain range climbs thousands of feet into the air.  Southward,
the roadway continues toward the hollow's end before beginning the
descent toward the far distant sea.  There is a new-looking @Rsign@n
planted beside the road.
