#2301
Roadway Across the Valley~
The road winds beside the crumbling edge of an old rock quarry leading
both to the north and south.  Some fifty feet below the trailway, the
dark sheen of water spreads across the quarry's bottom, its surface
smooth as glass.  Bleached white bones, reminders of those unfortunate
enough to have fallen to their deaths, rim the water's edge.  To the
north, the expanse of an ancient forest rises at the feet of the
mountains, the tall pines hazy blue in the distance.  There is a
new-looking @Rsign@n planted beside the road.
