#2312
Ruins of an Ancient Tower~
A tumbledown pile of rocks, blackened by a raging fire from years gone
by, is all that remains of what was once a prominent watchtower.  The
crumbling foundations give only a meagre indication of the tower's
original size; the weatherbeaten stone slabs lie no more than four high,
and then it is a rarity to see them in even a shadow of their former
glory.  The charred end of a torch lies splintered amidst the tower's
rubble, its braced length snapped like an inconsequential twig.  Standing
in the centre of the windswept debris, a solitary pine grows with
desperate hope for a time when the scars of this land will be healed by
nature.
